members.description: Appliance bay 2:The appliance has been reset.
The stacking health has changed to redundantly connected.
For uplink set Network_Uplink, uplink ports {"name":"CZJ9260730, interconnect 3","uri":"/rest/interconnects/5bd1f413-4507-4842-8fcc-3c76ad7b8bec"}: Q1, Q2 are non-operational.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Verify that the uplink ports used by the uplink set are enabled, linked, and correctly configured. Ensure the proper LAG and FEC configuration on upstream switches.

members.description: CZJ9260730, appliance bay 2 is no longer available or appliance services are migrating to CZJ9260730, appliance bay 1. CZJ9260730, appliance bay 1 is starting up to resume appliance operation.
The appliance cluster is no longer highly available.  CZJ9260730, appliance bay 2 is offline while applying an update.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: High availability protection will normally be restored automatically when the update completes.

members.description: Appliance starting.
All changes made on CZJ9260730, appliance bay 2 have been synchronized to CZJ9260730, appliance bay 1. The appliance cluster is now highly available.
Changes made on CZJ9260730, appliance bay 2 are being synchronized to CZJ9260730, appliance bay 1.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: No action is necessary. The appliance cluster will be highly available when synchronization completes.

members.description: Appliance bay 1:The appliance has been powered on.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: The appliance has been powered on. This event is sent because the appliance power on transition has occurred.

members.description: Appliance bay 1:The appliance has been reset.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: High availability protection will normally be restored automatically when the update completes.
